The paper deals with personalized acoustic modeling using deep learning techniques. The primary focus is on unsupervised learning of acoustic tokens from unlabeled data, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning (cs.SD). The paper also deals with speech recognition, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deep learning techniques for personalized modeling falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with acoustic modeling, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SD).
